-Binary- a system in which information can be expressed by combinations of the digits  0 and 1.
-In computers an on state when electricity is flowing represents true.the off statement on electricity flowing represents false.

-Boolean algebra - a branch of algebra that deals with boolean values true and false.
-Three fundamentals operations in boolean algebra

   * Not 
   * And
   * Or
-Not takes a single boolean values true or false.
-And boolean input takes two inputs and has a single output 
-Or gate - digital logic gate with two or more inputs and one output that logical operation.
-Exclusive Or - special type of binary operator that is used in logic, electronics  
